{
  "texts": [
    "Analogously to GSP, they provided a mapping from a poset to a minimal I-MAP DMAG and traverse poset space by making changes in the associated DMAG, moving to the poset associated with that new DMAG.",
    "In this case, the allowed change in the DMAG is changing a single bidirected edge into a directed one, or vice versa.",
    "Each of these moves in poset space results in a DMAG with the same or fewer edges.",
    "The authors conjectured, and supported with empirical evidence, that this algorithm produces a DMAG that is Markov equivalent to the true graph as N → ∞.",
    "Results on synthetic Gaussian net- works with between 10 and 50 variables, three of which are latent, showed better structural accuracy than FCI and FCI+."
  ]
}